ISSUE-002 | 2026-05-11
What went wrong: `neural_network_example/.venv` was accidentally added to a git
commit (~14k files, multi‑MB), so `git push` timed out or stalled. Virtualenvs
belong only on the developer machine.
How to avoid: Keep a repo root `.gitignore` with `.venv/` and `venv/`; run
`git rm -r --cached path/to/.venv` if one was staged; never `git add` inside
`.venv`. Rebuild envs with `pip install -r requirements.txt` after clone.

